				<td colspan="2"><span>After reading Reed's table, it looks like (and do correct me if I am wrong) that a low level character could actually gain the benefits of an intrument-driven song while using an instrument of a different type than is intentioned.
<br />

<br />
For example, looking at Reed's:
<br />

<br />
Selo's Accelerando uses Percussion Skill
<br />
- No Intrument, it has a mod of 1.0 (+23% Running Speed)
<br />
- w/Hand Drum, it has a mod of 1.8 (+41% Running Speed)
<br />
- w/Lute, it seems to still have a mod of 1.8 (+41% Running Speed?)
<br />

<br />
Now... am I reading this wrong?  If someone can clear this up, that would be most helpful.  If what I am reading is correct, then that should allow struggling young bards (like myself) work first on twisting alone without the added stress of instrument twisting.  I know that instrument twisting will be necessary later, but all the better if I can develop the needed manual dexterity in stages?
<br />
</span></td>
