			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Instruments<a name="7378"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 16 03 3:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tonedeph, sorry but yes you are reading that wrong.  What Reed's sheet means by the percentages is as follows:
<br />

<br />
For example, a level 5 bard playing Selos (5) with a hand drum (1.8 mod): +20/35/35/55% Run Speed
<br />

<br />
Sung - 20%
<br />
Epic - 35% (the sheet doesn't recognize a level 5 bard can't get their epic)
<br />
Hand Drum - 35% (both the hand drum and epic are 1.8 mod)
<br />
Puretone - 55% (again the sheet doesn't recognize a level 5 bard can't use Puretone, a level 60 discipline)
<br />

<br />
The confusion here is that the shading is for all instruments, the distinction in shading is for singing or instruments.  If you had a lute in hand and played selos, you would get the Sung percentage (20% in the example).  The way to tell what instrument a song uses is to look in Column B, Sk for Skill.  If it says P, you need to use percussion to get the Instrument modifier.
<br />

<br />
Hope that clears some things up,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
