				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Instruments<a name="7457"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 20 03 8:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tonedeph --
<br />

<br />
The other point that you missed is that the instrument played must match the type of instrument required for the song.  In your example, you suggest that a lute with a mod of 1.8 will increase your running speed with Selo's.  Actually, without a percussion instrument in your hand, you will receive no benefit from the lute when playing Selo's and are considered to have no instrument.
<br />

<br />
That is why the Bard epic is can be very valuable -- while it may only give a mod of 1.8, it gives it to all instrument types and your voice -- only one thing to carry around.  At the upper end of the game, you may encounter non-instrument items that will also provide you with an instrument bonus.  Their usefullness is often debated but don't worry about that now, just focus on learning how to play a bard.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=300110"">Rhondo Dolce</a>, 
New Dawnings of Fennin Ro, 
